definition.value: A 1-O-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl group is specified as lauroyl (dodecanoyl)
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the two acyl substituents at positions 1 and 2 are specified as lauroyl and arachidonoyl respectively.
A 1-O-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl group is specified as icosanoyl.
A mixture of exopolysaccharides and protein produced by most plants that plays a role in thickening membranes, storage of food and water, and seed germination.
A methanesulfonate (mesylate) salt prepared from equimolar amounts of nelfinavir and methanesulfonic acid. It is used for treatment of HIV and also exhibits some anticancer properties.
A phosphatidylcholine 40:4 in which the two acyl substituents at positions 1 and 2 are specified as icosanoyl and arachidonoyl respectively.
A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the amino to the phosphate group of 1-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (11Z,14Z,17Z,20Z,23Z)-3-oxohexacosapentaenoic acid.

A pentasaccharide derivative consisting of an alpha-D-glucosyl residue glycosidically linked to a 5-aminopentyl group and which carries at O-2 an alpha-L-rhamnosyl-(1->3)-[alpha-L-rhamnosyl-(1->3)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1->4)]-alpha-D-glucosyl branched tetrasaccharide unit
An N-acyl-L-homoserine lactone having 4-coumaroyl as the acyl substituent.
A phosphatidylethanolamine 38:5 obtained by transfer of a proton from the amino to the phosphate group of 1-oleoyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycerol-3-phosphoethanolamine.

A hexasaccharide derivative consisting of an alpha-D-mannosyl residue beta-linked to a 5-aminopentyl group and which carries at O-3 an beta-D-glucosyl-(1->3)-[beta-D-glucosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)-alpha-D-glucosyl-(1->4)]-N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl branched pentasaccharide unit.
A phosphatidylethanolamine 36:3 obtained by transfer of a proton from the amino to the phosphate group of 1-oleoyl-2-linoleoyl-sn-glycerol-3-phosphoethanolamine.
Triterpenoid saponins with a dammarane-like skeleton originally isolated from ginseng (Panax) species. Use of the term has been extended to include semi-synthetic derivatives.

A disaccharide derivative consisting of an N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminyl residue linked (1->3) to an alpha-D-glucoside residue, the anomeric carbon of which is linked to O-2 of D-glyceric acid and the O-6 of which is connecteded via a phospho linkage to a 5-aminopentyl group.
A dimeric disaccharide derivative formed from 2-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminopyranosyl-(1->3)-2-N-acetyl-6-(5-aminopentyl phosphoryl)-alpha-D-glucosaminopyranosyl-(1->2)-(2R)-3-hydroxypropanoate.

A branched pentasaccharide consisting of alpha-L-rhamnose, beta-D-glucose and two alpha-D-glucose residues in (1->3), (1->4) and (1->2) sequence, to the non-reducing-end glucose residue of which is also linked (1->3) an alpha-L-rhamnose residue.

An amino hexasaccharide comprising beta-D-glucose, N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosamine, alpha-D-glucose, N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosamine and alpha-D-mannose residues in (1->3), (1->4), (1->4) and (1->3) sequence, to the N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosamine residue contiguous to the reducing-end mannose residue of which is also linked (1->3) a further beta-D-glucose residue.
A glycosylglucose in which the glycosyl moiety is L-rhamnose linked alpha to C-3 of beta-D-glucose.

A tetrasaccharide comprising three alpha-D-mannose residues, all linked (1->2), with a beta-D-galactose residue also linked (1->4) to the reducing-end mannose residue. A Leishmania lipophosphoglycan capping tetrasaccharide.

A disaccharide derivative comprising two N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine residues linked (1->3), with a 6-aminopentylphospho group linked to each O-6 and with the anomeric carbon at the reducing end linked (1->2) to the O-2 of D-glyceric acid.
A phosphatidylethanolamine 36:2 obtained by transfer of a proton from the amino to the phosphate group of 1,2-dioleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine.
A  mannosylinositol phosphorylceramide(1-) in which either the acyl group is hydroxylated at position 2 or the ceramide base is hydroxylated at position 4.

A Man-1-6-Ins-1-P-Cer B/B'(1-) in which the acyl group and the ceramide base contain a total of 42 carbons and 0 double bonds, with either the acyl group hydroxylated at position 2 or the ceramide base hydroxylated at position 4.

A Man-1-6-Ins-1-P-Cer B/B'(1-) in which the acyl group and the ceramide base contain a total of 44 carbons and 0 double bonds, with either the acyl group hydroxylated at position 2 or the ceramide base hydroxylated at position 4.
A dipeptide formed from L-tyrosine and glycine residues.
A tripeptide composed of one L-tyrosine and two glycine residues joined in sequence.
A monomethoxyflavone that is quercetin methylated at position 7.
A dipeptide formed from L-tyrosine and L-isoleucine residues.
A mannosylinositol phosphorylceramide in which the acyl group is hydroxylated at position 2 and the ceramide base is hydroxylated at position 4.

A Man-1-6-Ins-1-P-Cer C(1-) in which the acyl group and the ceramide base contain a total of 42 carbons and 0 double bonds, with the acyl group hydroxylated at position 2 and the ceramide base hydroxylated at position 4.

A Man-1-6-Ins-1-P-Cer C(1-) in which the acyl group and the ceramide base contain a total of 42 carbons and 0 double bonds, with the acyl group hydroxylated at position 2 and the ceramide base hydroxylated at position 4.
An organophosphate oxoanion resulting from the deprotonation of both of the phosphate groups of mannosyl diphosphorylinositol ceramide. The major species at pH 7.3.
An Ins-1-P-6-Man-1-6-Ins-1-P-Cer(2-) in which the acyl group is not hydroxylated at position 2 and the ceramide base is not hydroxylated at position 4.

An Ins-1-P-6-Man-1-6-Ins-1-P-Cer A(2-) in which the acyl group and the ceramide base contain a total of 44 carbons and 0 double bonds, and in which the acyl group is not hydroxylated at position 2 and the ceramide base is not hydroxylated at position 4.
A piperidine alkaloid that is piperidine substituted by a 2-oxo-3-[(2R)-piperidin-2-yl]propyl group at position 2.

A flavone C-glycoside that is flavone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 5, 7, 3' and 4' and a beta-D-glucopyranosyl and a beta-L-arabinopyranosyl residue via C-glycosidic linkages at positions 6 and 8 respectively
An Ins-1-P-6-Man-1-6-Ins-1-P-Cer(2-) in which either the acyl group is hydroxylated at position 2 or the ceramide base is hydroxylated at position 4.

An Ins-1-P-6-Man-1-6-Ins-1-P-Cer B/B'(2-) in which the acyl group and the ceramide base contain a total of 42 carbons and 0 double bonds, with either the acyl group hydroxylated at position 2 or the ceramide base hydroxylated at position 4.

An Ins-1-P-6-Man-1-6-Ins-1-P-Cer B/B'(2-) in which the acyl group and the ceramide base contain a total of 44 carbons and 0 double bonds, with either the acyl group hydroxylated at position 2 or the ceramide base hydroxylated at position 4.
A dipeptide formed from L-tyrosine and L-leucine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-tyrosine and L-lysine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-tyrosine and L-phenylalanine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-tyrosine and L-tryptophan residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-tyrosine and L-valine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-valine and L-alanine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-valine and L-aspartic acid residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-valine and L-glutamine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-valine and L-glutamic acid residues.
